50|$|Thirteen {{individuals}} were charged and tried {{in connection with}} the killings, four were convicted <b>in</b> <b>absentia</b> <b>in</b> Belgrade. The other eleven were tried and convicted <b>in</b> <b>absentia</b> <b>in</b> Gospić. One of those convicted by Gospić County Court subsequently returned to Croatia, where he was granted a retrial and acquitted. A monument dedicated to the victims of the massacre was built in the village in 2003.|$|R
