5000|$|Trial <b>in</b> <b>absentia</b> is a {{criminal}} proceeding {{in a court of}} law in which the person who is subject to it is not physically present at those proceedings. <b>In</b> <b>absentia</b> is Latin for [...] "in the absence". Its meaning varies by jurisdiction and legal system.|$|R
